<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0d8cbfd4-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s20101"><num value="20101">§ 20101.</num><heading> Congressional declaration of purpose</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">It is the intention of Congress in enacting this chapter to promote the fundamental right to vote by improving access for handicapped and elderly individuals to registration facilities and polling places for Federal elections.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id0d8cbfd5-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/435/s2">Pub. L. 98–435, § 2</ref>, <date date="1984-09-28">Sept. 28, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/1678">98 Stat. 1678</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id0d8cbfd6-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id0d8cbfd7-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id0d8cbfd8-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s1973ee">section 1973ee of Title 42</ref>, The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id0d8cbfd9-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="id0d8cbfda-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p><ref href="/us/pl/98/435/s9">Pub. L. 98–435, § 9</ref>, <date date="1984-09-28">Sept. 28, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/1680">98 Stat. 1680</ref>, provided that: <quotedContent origin="/us/pl/98/435/s9">“This Act [enacting this chapter] shall apply with respect to elections taking place after <date date="1985-12-31">December 31, 1985</date>.”</quotedContent>
</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
